'''Whimper Save''' was a mysterious [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Gender/Legends|female]] who, in [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]], was on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] inside the [[Outlander Club/Legends|Outlander Club]] with the [[Con artist/Legends|con artist]] [[Dannl Faytonni/Legends|Dannl Faytonni]] at the same time as the [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunters]] [[Jango Fett/Legends|Jango Fett]] and [[Zam Wesell/Legends|Zam Wesell]]. Sometime later, she was talking with Faytonni at the bar of the Outlander when Wesell entered the club trying to [[Plot to assassinate Senator Amidala/Legends|escape]] from the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] and [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]]. She turned to stare when Wesell's [[Limb/Legends|arm]] was [[Dismemberment/Legends|cut off]] by Kenobi.

==Biography==
[[File:FaytonniReinaWhimper-AOTC.png|thumb|left|300px|Save, Faytonni, and March turned to stare at Wesell.]]
Whimper Save was a mysterious<ref name="Insider" /> [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Gender/Legends|female]].<ref name="DB" /> In [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]],<ref name="NEC Note">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' dates the events of [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones'']] to [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]]. The scene from ''[[Jango Fett: Bounty Hunter]]'' in which [[Jango Fett/Legends|Jango Fett]] is in the [[Outlander Club/Legends|Outlander Club]] takes place shortly before the film's [[Plot to assassinate Senator Amidala/Legends|assassination attempt]] on [[Senator/Legends|Senator]] [[Padmé Amidala/Legends|Padmé Amidala]].</ref> she<ref name="Insider" /> was on<ref name="Jango Fett: Bounty Hunter" /> the [[Planet/Legends|planet]]<ref name="TVD">''[[Star Wars: Attack of the Clones: The Visual Dictionary]]''</ref> [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]], visiting the [[Outlander Club/Legends|Outlander Club]],<ref name="Jango Fett: Bounty Hunter" /> a [[Nightclub/Legends|nightclub]] and [[Gambling/Legends|gambling]] hall<ref name="CSWE2">{{CSWECite|II|431|Outlander Club}}</ref> in the [[Uscru Entertainment District/Legends|Uscru Entertainment District]] of Coruscant.<ref name="FF44">{{FactFile|44|COR 21-22|Coruscant &ndash; Outlander Club}}</ref> She was in the company of<ref name="Jango Fett: Bounty Hunter" /> the [[Con artist/Legends|con artist]] [[Dannl Faytonni/Legends|Dannl Faytonni]]<ref name="DB2">{{DB|character|lieutenantfaytonni|Faytonni, Lieutenant Dannl}}</ref> and<ref name="Jango Fett: Bounty Hunter" /> the anarchist criminal [[Reina March]].<ref name="DB3">{{DB|character|reinamarch|March, Reina}}</ref> The group was at the club the same time as the [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunters]] [[Jango Fett/Legends|Jango Fett]] and [[Zam Wesell/Legends|Zam Wesell]], who were there planning an assassination on [[Senator/Legends|Senator]] [[Padmé Amidala/Legends|Padmé Amidala]].<ref name="Jango Fett: Bounty Hunter" />

Shortly after<ref name="NEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' dates the events of {{Film|II}} to [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]].</ref> at [[Local day/Legends|night]], Save was once again in the Outlander Club with Faytonni and March when Wesell ran inside the club to escape from the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] and [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] after trying to [[Plot to assassinate Senator Amidala/Legends|assassinate]] Amidala.<ref name="AoTC" /> Save drank at the club's bar<ref name="IA">{{SWArchive|url=episode-ii/explore/attack/2002/11/imageattack20021126.html|series=Image Attack|text=Good Save}}</ref> and talked with Faytonni. When Kenobi made his way to the bar, a Human joined the trio and talked with March as Save watched her. When the Human left, Save turned her attention back to Faytonni, with whom she was holding hands with. A short while later, Save stared when Wesell's [[Limb/Legends|arm]] was [[Dismemberment/Legends|cut off]] by Kenobi in an unsuccessful ambush. As Wesell was being helped up by the Jedi, a smiling Save started talking with Faytonni again. Skywalker then told the clubgoers to go back to their drinks.<ref name="AoTC" />

==Personality and traits==
Save was an enigmatic<ref name="DB" /> and mysterious individual who was considered beautiful.<ref name="Insider" /> She had [[Color/Legends|light]] skin, dark [[Hair/Legends|hair]], and brown [[Eye/Legends|eyes]].<ref name="DB" /> It was unclear whether or not she was an associate of the con artist or if she was taken in by his [[Republic Security Force/Legends|security officer]] ruse.<ref name="Insider" />

==Equipment==
Unlike other Outlander Club patrons,<ref name="Insider" /> Save wore a dark,<ref name="AoTC" /> hooded [[Clothing/Legends|outfit]]<ref name="Insider" /> during her visits to the club.<ref name="Jango Fett: Bounty Hunter" /><ref name="AoTC" />

==Behind the scenes==
{{Quote|The votes are in for the “Best Name in Episode II" awards, with Whimper Save edging out Jedi Knight Bultar Swan to win top honors in the so-unofficial-we-just-made-it-up competition.|Daniel Wallace|<ref name="Insider" />}}
[[File:Faytonni_ep2dvd.jpg|thumb|right|300px|The uncredited extra playing Save on set.]]
Whimper Save was created for the [[prequel trilogy]] film [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones'']],<ref name="AoTC" /> which released on [[May 16]], [[2002]].<ref name="Year">''[[Star Wars Year by Year: A Visual Chronicle]]''</ref> The Outlander Club scenes, where Save was portrayed by an uncredited extra, were shot at [[Fox Studios, Sydney]] on [[July 17]], [[2000]].<ref name="Mythmaking">''[[Mythmaking: Behind the Scenes of Attack of the Clones]]''</ref> Prior to the film's release, Save was first pictured in the documentary "[[Making Episode II Webdocs|A Twinkle Beyond Pluto]],"<ref name="ATBP">{{SW|url=video/a-twinkle-beyond-pluto|series=Making Episode II Webdocs|text=Part 5: A Twinkle Beyond Pluto}}</ref> released on [[July 31]], [[2001]].<ref name="ATBP Date">{{SWArchive|url=episode-ii/bts/me2/archive.html|text=''Making Episode II Webdocs'' archive}}</ref> Save then first appeared in illustrations for both the film's [[Star Wars: Attack of the Clones Movie Storybook|storybook]], written by [[Jane Mason]] and [[Sarah Hines Stephens]],<ref name="Storybook">''[[Star Wars: Attack of the Clones Movie Storybook]]''</ref> and the young readers book ''[[Jango Fett: Bounty Hunter]]'', written by [[Eric Arnold]] and illustrated by [[Valerie Reckert]].<ref name="Jango Fett: Bounty Hunter">''[[Jango Fett: Bounty Hunter]]''</ref> Both books were published on [[April 23]], 2002.<ref name="Amazon">{{SWArchive|url=eu/lit/young/news20020225.html|text=Book Preview: Episode II Children's Books}}</ref>

Whimper Save was first identified though the [[Image Attack]] feature on [[StarWars.com]] on [[November 26]], 2002.<ref name="IA" /> In the [[May 2]], [[2003]], [[StarWars.com]] web article "[[Cantina Roll-Call: Shedding Light on Some Alien Aliases]]," Save is incorrectly identified as a different Outlander Club patron.<ref name="crc">{{SWArchive|url=episode-iv/bts/article/f20030502/index.html|text=Cantina Roll-Call: Shedding Light on Some Alien Aliases|int=Cantina Roll-Call: Shedding Light on Some Alien Aliases}}</ref> In the article "[[Who's Who in the Outlander Club: It's Ladies' Night]]," published in the [[Star Wars Insider 75|seventy-fifth issue]] of the ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine on [[April 6]], [[2004]],<ref name="SW.com">{{SWArchive|url=community/fanclub/mag/news20040315.html|text=The New Face of Evil}}</ref> author [[Daniel Wallace]] pokes fun at Save's name, writing that Save beat out [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]] [[Bultar Swan/Legends|Bultar Swan]] to win the "Best Name in Episode II" competition.<ref name="Insider" />

